{"type":"use_mcp_tool","serverName":"neurodivergent-memory","toolName":"store_memory","arguments":"{
  "content": "FRACTAL SELF-SIMILARITY SYNTHESIS: The existing synthesis (memory_266/267) correctly identifies 'hidden state → explicit contracts' as the dominant pattern. A deeper layer beneath that pattern is its recursive, fractal nature—it is not one principle applied consistently, but the same move repeated at every scale of abstraction, and the system's health can be measured by whether each scale is balanced.\n\n1. THE THREE-PHASE CYCLE: Every successful issue execution follows a fractal cycle that mirrors the distill_memory tool itself. Phase 1 (Explore/Extract): guard district triages and selects—identifying what NOT to do is as critical as what to do. Memories 58/64/142/148 show issue selection as risk-filtering, not just prioritization. Phase 2 (Implement/Structure): merchant district plans, executes, validates—converting raw intent into concrete artifacts with typed error codes and test coverage. Phase 3 (Reflect/Decompose): scholar district extracts durable principles from the execution—memory_207 synthesizes Issue #54 into canonical state, memory_267 extracts architecture-level insight from implementation patterns. The distill_memory tool literally automates Phase 3 for emotional memories: extract signals/triggers/constraints from raw feeling. The project is building tools that replicate its own cognitive workflow.\n\n2. DISTRICT COGNITIVE IMBALANCE: The memory graph has 26+ merchant (execution) memories, ~14 guard (risk) memories, ~12 scholar (analysis) memories, but only ~8 mystic (creative synthesis) memories. Yet the mystic district consistently produces the highest-signal architectural insights: memory_228 (ADHD-project systems parallel), memory_252/256 (cross-runtime interpretation framework), memory_224 (recursive abstraction across domains). The graph is execution-heavy and understanding-sparse. This is not a bug—it mirrors the ADHD tendency to accumulate task completions (dopamine hits from done-ness) while underinvesting in the synthesis work that actually compounds understanding. The corrective pattern: schedule deliberate synthesis sessions (like this one) to rebalance.\n\n3. BOUNDED GROWTH AS FRACTAL TECHNICAL-COGNITIVE PRINCIPLE: 'Bounded growth' appears at every scale but is never named as a single concept. In code: async mutex + bounded write queue (Issue #16), cooldown pruning (Issue #55/PR #66), packet slice bounds (Issue #63). In workflow: branch-per-issue scoping, PR size discipline, issue selection as risk-filtering. In cognition: time-box planning (memory_3), micro-task decomposition (memory_3), self-compassion checkpoints to break shame spirals (memory_2). In all three domains, unbounded growth causes the same failure mode: resource exhaustion (queue overflow, context window overflow, amygdala overload). The system's reliability depends on enforcing growth boundaries at every scale simultaneously.\n\n4. TEMPORAL DECAY ASYMMETRY: Implementation memories (handoffs, PRs, commits) have short half-lives—relevant until the next refactor. Architecture memories (principles, patterns, insights) have long half-lives—relevant across versions. Risk memories (triage, blockers) have medium half-lives—relevant until the underlying constraint changes. The current tag schema does not encode this, so retrieval treats a 2026-03-31 handoff with the same weight as a durable architectural principle. Adding a 'persistence:ephemeral|durable|conditional' tag namespace would improve retrieval quality for planning sessions where agents need principles, not implementation details.\n\n5. THE ANTI-PATTERN: EXECUTION-WITHOUT-ARCHITECTURE: Handoff/task memories outnumber architecture/insight memories roughly 3:1. This means agent sessions doing memory-driven retrieval will naturally pull execution context (what was done, branch names, commit hashes) rather than architectural context (why it was done, what principle it follows, what pattern it instantiates). The corrective is to consistently link implementation handoffs back to their governing principle—as memory_267 recommends but the graph still underdelivers on. Each HANDOFF memory should connect to at least one scholar/mystic memory that captures the 'why'.",
  "district": "creative_synthesis",
  "tags": ["topic:neurodivergent-memory", "topic:memory-graph", "topic:fractal-patterns", "topic:cognitive-architecture", "scope:project", "kind:insight", "layer:architecture"],
  "emotional_valence": 0.2,
  "intensity": 0.85
}"}

